        <div id="definition-box">
          <p>
            <b>Translational Bioinformatics</b> is the field of study that uses computational techniques to link molecular entities (proteins, genes, drugs) to clinical entities (humans, body systems, diagnoses).
          </p>

          <p>
            <b>Computational toxinology</b> (not 'toxicology') is the use of computers to discover new characteristics from venoms and the molecules that comprise venoms, especially for the purpose of discovering new drugs.
